---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="About — Susan Denim" description="I know what you did and what you get away with every single day.">
<div class="z1" style="max-width:680px;margin:0 auto;padding:4rem 1.5rem;">

  <!-- Portrait placeholder — replace with Canva export -->
  <div style="display:flex;align-items:flex-start;gap:2.5rem;margin-bottom:3rem;flex-wrap:wrap;">
    <div style="width:140px;height:140px;border-radius:50%;background:var(--surface);border:2px solid var(--border);flex-shrink:0;overflow:hidden;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;">
      <img id="susan-portrait" src="/susan-denim.jpg" alt="Susan Denim" style="width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;" onerror="this.style.display='none';document.getElementById('susan-initials').style.display='flex'" />
      <div id="susan-initials" style="display:none;width:100%;height:100%;align-items:center;justify-content:center;font-size:2.5rem;font-weight:900;color:var(--muted);">SD</div>
    </div>
    <div style="flex:1;min-width:200px;">
      <h1 style="font-size:clamp(1.8rem,4vw,2.4rem);font-weight:900;color:var(--blade);letter-spacing:-.04em;margin-bottom:.25rem;">Susan Denim</h1>
      <div style="font-size:.82rem;color:var(--muted2);margin-bottom:1rem;">LittleFuckYourself, Devon</div>
      <blockquote style="font-size:1.05rem;color:var(--text);font-style:italic;line-height:1.65;margin:0;border-left:3px solid var(--red);padding-left:1rem;">
        I know what you did and what you get away with every single day.
      </blockquote>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Bio -->
  <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:1.25rem;font-size:.95rem;color:var(--muted2);line-height:1.8;">
    <p>
      Claimour exists because the information asymmetry between institutions and individuals is not accidental.
      It is engineered. Banks train thousands of staff to handle complaints. You get a letter, a helpline, and a 56-day clock.
    </p>
    <p>
      The Grimoires were compiled from 260 app teardowns over three years of documenting what technology actually does
      versus what it claims to do. The LifeBack UK guides were written after watching people lose housing, credit,
      and dignity to processes that depended entirely on their not knowing the rules.
    </p>
    <p>
      The Bank Hypocrisy Watch exists because I am tired of reading Mental Health Awareness Week press releases
      from organisations that spent the other 51 weeks doing the opposite.
    </p>
    <p>
      The Oracle is opinionated. So am I.
    </p>
    <p style="color:var(--muted);">
      I do not provide legal advice. I provide what I know, what I think, and the tools to act on both.
      The sword is yours. Use it.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Contact -->
  <div style="margin-top:3rem;padding:1.5rem;border:1px solid var(--border);border-left:3px solid var(--red);border-radius:5px;">
    <div style="font-size:.78rem;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:.75rem;">Contact</div>
    <div style="font-size:.88rem;color:var(--muted2);line-height:1.7;">
      Evidence for the Bank Watch: <a href="mailto:receipts@claimour.com" style="color:var(--red);">receipts@claimour.com</a><br/>
      Everything else: <a href="mailto:susan@claimour.com" style="color:var(--red);">susan@claimour.com</a><br/>
      <span style="color:var(--muted);font-size:.78rem;">I read everything. I reply to very little. If your situation is urgent, go to <a href="/oracle" style="color:var(--gold);">The Oracle</a> first.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

</div>
</Layout>
